This is an excerpt from the Cherokee Supreme Court docket for the years 1823 to 1834. The Cherokee Supreme Court convened annually in New Echota beginning on the second Monday in October and lasting three weeks. This excerpt is from the Tuesday November 1, 1825 session of court. Entries from this Supreme Court docket cover items ch100-ch163.

body.value: Tuesday 1st of November Court convened agreeable to adjournment Present their Honors John Martin &C et cetera Jurors G. George Saunders Fore Foreman It is the opinion of the Jury that John Walker snr senior shall pay Betsey Broon for her negroe negro . G. Saunders, Fore Judgement in favor of Jackson & McConnel against Bridge Maker & wife by default $19.12 Â½ Judgement against Taylor Eldridge & William Blythe in favor of Jacob Seabolt , by default $51.75 Judgement in favor of Horsefly against John Spears by default Court is adjourned untill until tomorrow 10 Oclock
